---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'July 21, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Voq"
  description="Voq's privacy policy: by default Voq reads webpage text using your browser's built-in voice, with an optional limited-use natural voice powered by Google Cloud Text-to-Speech, and an optional paid subscription processed by Stripe."
>
  <div class="container">
    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        Voq is a free Chrome extension that reads webpage text aloud, with an optional paid
        subscription for unlimited natural voice. This page explains what data Voq does — and
        does not — handle.
      </p>

      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Voq does not collect any personal data.</li>
        <li>Voq does not require an account or sign-up, even for the paid subscription.</li>
        <li>Voq has no analytics, tracking, or advertising of any kind.</li>
        <li>By default, Voq reads text using your browser's built-in voice, entirely on your device.</li>
        <li>For a limited daily amount of natural-sounding speech, selected text is sent securely to Voq's own relay service and Google Cloud Text-to-Speech to generate audio, then immediately discarded.</li>
        <li>Removing the daily limit is optional and paid for through Stripe — Voq never sees or stores your card details.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Voq works</h2>
      <p>
        Voq offers two ways to read text aloud.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Standard voice (default):</strong> When you select text and choose to have it read aloud,
        Voq passes that text directly to your browser's built-in
        <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Speech_API" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Speech API</a>,
        which converts it to speech on your device. The text never leaves your browser.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Natural voice (limited daily use, or unlimited with a paid subscription):</strong> To offer a
        more natural-sounding voice, Voq can optionally send selected text to Voq's own relay service, which
        forwards it to Google Cloud Text-to-Speech to generate audio. The audio is returned to your browser
        and played immediately. The text is not stored by Voq or by Google after the audio is generated. On
        the free tier this is limited to a small amount of use per day, after which Voq automatically reverts
        to the standard on-device voice; an optional paid subscription removes that daily limit.
      </p>

      <h2>Data collection</h2>
      <p>
        Voq does not collect, store, or transmit any of the following:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your browsing history</li>
        <li>Personal information, such as your name, email, or IP address</li>
        <li>Usage analytics or telemetry</li>
        <li>Any text read using the standard on-device voice</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        When natural voice is used, the selected text is transmitted solely to generate audio and is
        not logged or stored by Voq. Voq keeps a small daily usage counter (how many characters of
        natural voice have been used today), tied to a randomly generated device identifier that is not
        linked to your identity in any way. If you have an active paid subscription, that same device
        identifier and your subscription's activation code are stored to keep your subscription active.
        These are stored using Chrome's built-in <code>storage.sync</code>, which means they are saved
        under your Google account and can sync across Chrome browsers you're signed into — the same way
        any other extension setting syncs. Voq does not use this data for anything beyond activating and
        verifying your subscription.
      </p>
      <p>
        Voq does not use cookies, does not include any third-party trackers, and does not sell or
        share data with any third party.
      </p>

      <h2>Paid subscription (optional)</h2>
      <p>
        Voq offers an optional paid subscription that removes the daily limit on natural voice.
        Payment is handled entirely by <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe</a>,
        a third-party payment processor — Voq redirects you to Stripe's own secure checkout page to
        complete payment, and Voq never receives, sees, or stores your card number or other payment
        details.
      </p>
      <p>
        A subscription is limited to one active device at a time. If a device goes unused for about a
        week, its activation automatically frees up so the subscription can be activated on another
        device instead — this happens entirely on Voq's backend and involves no personal data, just the
        anonymous device identifier described above.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cancelling is self-service: the extension links directly to Stripe's own billing portal, so Voq
        never needs your email or any other identifying information to process a cancellation.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        When natural voice is used, text is processed by
        <a href="https://cloud.google.com/text-to-speech" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Cloud Text-to-Speech</a>
        solely to generate audio. Google's handling of this data is governed by
        <a href="https://cloud.google.com/terms/cloud-privacy-notice" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Cloud's privacy terms</a>.
        Voq does not send any personally identifying information alongside this text.
      </p>
      <p>
        For the optional paid subscription, payments are processed by
        <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe</a>. Stripe's handling
        of your payment data is governed by Stripe's own privacy policy, linked above.
      </p>

      <h2>Permissions</h2>
      <p>
        Voq requests only the browser permissions it needs to read the
        current page's text aloud, display its reading controls, and
        optionally generate natural-sounding audio. These permissions are
        used solely to provide that functionality and are never used to
        collect data for any other purpose.
      </p>

      <h2>Accounts</h2>
      <p>
        Voq does not require you to create a Voq account or sign in with an email or password —
        this is true for the free tier and the paid subscription alike. To keep a paid subscription
        working when you reinstall the extension or switch computers, Voq relies on your existing
        Google/Chrome sign-in via Chrome's sync storage; it does not create or require any separate
        account of its own.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Voq does not knowingly collect any personal data from anyone,
        including children.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this privacy policy ever changes, the updated version will be
        posted on this page with a revised "Last updated" date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy, you can reach out
        via the contact information listed on Voq's Chrome Web Store
        listing.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
